      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add Skill Workshop and skill research",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nThis PR moves Skill Workshop into the core skills subsystem and makes it the governed path for creating, revising, reviewing, and applying OpenClaw skill proposals.\r\n\r\nAgents now use `skill_workshop` for skill proposal work. Skill Research is kept as a separate internal layer for autonomous durable-instruction capture; when it detects reusable skill work, it queues a pending Workshop proposal instead of writing live skills directly.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1204\" height=\"600\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/deaa89b2-0354-42a8-8e24-042521e0e3a0\" />\r\n<img width=\"1211\" height=\"641\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/91395569-10c5-48c7-adea-7138c667e071\" />\r\n<img width=\"1303\" height=\"848\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b64f0904-ac02-4a48-a574-9598f92b7d98\" />\r\n<img width=\"1187\" height=\"561\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/cec0389c-a9ec-4848-b705-e06839e6d471\" />\r\n\r\n## What changed\r\n\r\n- Added durable Skill Workshop proposal storage under OpenClaw state, with `proposal.json`, `PROPOSAL.md`, support files, rollback metadata, and a rebuildable `proposals.json` manifest.\r\n- Added the `skill_workshop` agent tool for create, update, revise, list, inspect, apply, reject, and quarantine actions.\r\n- Added CLI commands under `openclaw skills workshop`.\r\n- Added Gateway proposal methods for list, inspect, create, update, apply, reject, and quarantine flows.\r\n- Added proposal support files under standard skill folders, with text-file validation, scanner checks, hash verification, stale-target detection, and guarded apply writes.\r\n- Added proposal revision support with versioned and dated proposal frontmatter.\r\n- Added Skill Research auto-capture as a separate internal layer that queues Workshop proposals when autonomous capture is enabled.\r\n- Added system prompt/tool catalog guidance so agents route skill creation and proposal lifecycle work through `skill_workshop`.\r\n- Removed the old Skill Workshop plugin package now that Workshop is core skills functionality.\r\n- Added docs and changelog entries for the proposal lifecycle.\r\n\r\n## Behavior\r\n\r\n- Generated skills are pending proposals by default.\r\n- Active skills are not overwritten silently.\r\n- Apply is workspace-scoped and checks stale target state before writing.\r\n- Update proposals preserve target baselines and mark stale when live skill/support files change.\r\n- Support files are validated, scanned, hash-checked, and rejected when unsafe or non-text.\r\n- Apply writes rollback metadata and uses guarded writes to avoid partial or clobbering publishes.\r\n- Reject and quarantine only operate on pending proposals.\r\n\r\n## Verification\r\n\r\n- `git diff --check`\r\n- AWS Crabbox `cbx_d2a8fac69de8`:\r\n  `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/tools/skill-workshop-tool.test.ts src/skills/research/autocapture.test.ts src/agents/harness/agent-end-side-effects.test.ts src/agents/agent-tools.before-tool-call.embedded-mode.test.ts src/agents/system-prompt.test.ts src/agents/tool-catalog.test.ts src/agents/agent-tools.create-openclaw-coding-tools.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt-tool-construction-plan.test.ts packages/gateway-protocol/src/schema/agents-models-skills.test.ts src/skills/workshop/service.test.ts`\r\n- AWS Crabbox `cbx_d2a8fac69de8`:\r\n  `pnpm check:changed -- <changed paths>`\r\n",
        "branch": "feat/skill-workshop-proposals",
